  "description": {
    "en": "The moose is the largest member of the deer family, famous for the enormous, flat antlers of the males.",
    "zh": "驼鹿是鹿科动物中体型最大的，以雄性巨大的扁平鹿角而闻名。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Moose are the tallest members of the deer family, standing up to 2.1 meters at the shoulder and weighing up to 700 kilograms. Male moose grow enormous palmate antlers that can span 1.8 meters wide and are shed and regrown every year. They have long legs, a drooping nose, and a flap of skin called a dewlap hanging under the chin.",
      "zh": "驼鹿是鹿科动物中最高的，肩高可达2.1米，体重可达700公斤。雄性驼鹿长着巨大的掌状鹿角，宽度可达1.8米，每年脱落后重新长出来。它们有长长的腿、下垂的鼻子，下巴下面还挂着一块叫做「肉垂」的皮肤。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Moose are herbivores that feed on leaves, bark, twigs, and aquatic plants. They are excellent swimmers and can dive underwater to eat water plants from the bottom of lakes. Despite their calm appearance, moose can be very aggressive, especially mothers protecting their calves.",
      "zh": "驼鹿是草食动物，吃树叶、树皮、嫩枝和水生植物。它们是出色的游泳者，可以潜入水下吃湖底的水草。尽管驼鹿看起来很温和，但它们其实可能非常凶猛，尤其是保护小鹿的母驼鹿。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Moose live in boreal and mixed forests across North America, Europe, and Asia. In North America, they are found in Alaska, Canada, and the northern United States. They prefer areas near lakes, ponds, and wetlands where they can cool off and find aquatic food.",
      "zh": "驼鹿生活在北美洲、欧洲和亚洲的北方针叶林和混交林中。在北美洲，它们分布在阿拉斯加、加拿大和美国北部。它们喜欢靠近湖泊、池塘和湿地的地方，可以在那里乘凉和寻找水生食物。"
    }
  },
